Rear Admiral Alan Green (born 19 December 1952) <ref name="CV">{{cite web | url=http://www.armscomm.org.za/hearings/witness-statements/ws-Admiral-Alan-Green.pdf | title=Statement and CV of Alan Green | publisher=The Arms Procurement commission | accessdate=July 24, 2014}}</ref> is a retired South African Navy officer who served as Chief: Military Policy, Strategy and Planning for the [[South African National Defence Force]]. He retired in 2012.<ref name="CV" />
His awards and honours include the [[Medal for Distinguished Conduct and Loyal Service]] for 40 years service.<ref name="Medals">{{cite web | url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=29441:western-cape-sandf-members-receive-medals&catid=111:sa-defence&Itemid=242 | title=Western Cape SANDF members receive medals | publisher=Defenceweb | date=February 13, 2013 | accessdate=October 31, 2014 | author=Wingrin, Dean}}</ref>
He commanded the [[Warrior class strike craft]] {{SAS|Job Masego}} (previously SAS Kobie Koetzee) in 1988.<ref>http://152.111.1.87/argief/berigte/dieburger/1988/07/23/3/2.html</ref> ==References== {{reflist}}
